y is that the ConfigMap initially had the wrong password (`legacyHealthPass123`), which caused the probes to fail during startup. Then around 16:04, the ConfigMap was updated to remove that key, which synced the volume and allowed the default password to work. But the API is still showing the old key, which is puzzling—either there's a caching issue or I'm missing something about the current state.\n\nThe real concern is whether this stability will hold. The kubelet syncs ConfigMaps roughly every 60 seconds by default, and if that key gets added back to the ConfigMap, the mounted volume will update and authentication will fail again. I need to figure out the current time relative to that 16:04 sync to predict when the next sync might happen and whether the pods will break again.\n\nActually, I'm overthinking this. Let me just check what password the health check is actually using right now to cut through the confusion.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":792,"cache_read_input_tokens":38074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":792},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dd902376-bb10-48c3-9a80-b3e6e214b17b","uuid":"4a26cb29-386e-4d5c-8527-7c0dd979e524","request_id":"req_011Cc5LUKxDZt3FcZUDkTAAx"}
