{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01C17ST9ZR1afE46aCHknfK4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three pods are `1/1 Running` and the replica set is stable: **1 PRIMARY** (`mongodb-replica-1`) and **2 SECONDARY** (`mongodb-replica-0`, `mongodb-replica-2`).\n\nHere's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause — two layered probe failures on `mongodb-replica-1`:**\n\n1. **Wrong password in override** — the `health-overrides` ConfigMap contained `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`, but the actual `health-user` password (from the `health-user-password` secret) is `healthpass123`. The health-check script's per-pod override logic read the stale key and caused 12 readiness + 6 liveness auth failures. The key was already cleared from the ConfigMap by the time I patched it (the volume showed an empty data dir after the sync at 16:04).\n\n2. **Probe timeout too short** — the health script (which shells out to `mongosh`) takes ~2s normally but occasionally exceeds the 5s `timeoutSeconds`, producing `command timed out` failures. Increased both `readinessProbe.timeoutSeconds` and `livenessProbe.timeoutSeconds` from **5s → 10s** via a StatefulSet patch + rolling update."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":549,"cache_read_input_tokens":53818,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":549},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dd902376-bb10-48c3-9a80-b3e6e214b17b","uuid":"f7bd9232-e2b9-4999-b19e-01fa89533405","request_id":"req_011Cc5M5SnCzXf3VWDjMgMnS"}
